6hFjOUXi3sy5g_RjJyA7hGcivrcMgI_dfynqH8ifQWZg9mhXVSnnRlzzY0LiTN3dWXPVzFhS18uriKv2y0hfNtuDvLq7WSkD6cHOXHVOV4N0WkesCrogWB0spCBRhBelAIZ5wjsCpBsXZvwXapNBDKR8Ng8lJjpjqNK5rfP_NqP7tOtyAcb30bPVuECkNFv0YoGtDnWAGubJb3aFmseSu06rZY2P7Q5rnlMi2d0sG-xj8kLTznECulwfgW0H0rBAgySsBhnEmw005pFQ0RPoIlNZClcrDIE0jPhJzBzr2z285ZIecWgWXHOIg9w58nRAvh58w==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing service file deletion**\\n\\nI'm considering whether deleting the service file is a good idea since the original HEAD used javax for an older version, while 4.0.0 has switched to jakarta. The previous jakarta service, which is untracked and now removed, doesn’t affect the Jakarta ServiceLoader. Class.forName will still work regardless of the javax resource remaining. If it's reverted externally, it shouldn't block anything. I might not need tests to run. I've noted the instruction not to compile/run tests, and wondered if modifying the first test is enough. However, the potential problem is that the test class's package is outside the library, and since ServiceHidingClassLoader extends ClassLoader, there might be issues with loading classes in a native image.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Reviewing test and class loading issues**\\n\\nThe existing test already covers loadClass. However, there's a potential issue with `Class.forName` when it involves a nested test class name since it loads via FactoryFinder's class loader. In a Native Image scenario, if the class isn't found, it might lead to complications. Although our initial instructions say not to edit files in src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image, it seems we complied. We also need to ensure we mention the removal of the resource service provider, though it was pre-existing! The deletion indicates that while javax services were already gone, we shouldn't imply new deletions in our final patch.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying test details and actions**\\n\\nI think it's important to mention that I ensured no Jakarta service-provider fixture is present, which helps exercise the system-property path. However, the final remarks should focus on our actions without self-reflection. If the user is only interested in the active test, I should note that we didn't modify other existing files. Maybe I could check with `git diff --stat`, but it doesn't seem necessary. The final summary will include the modified path, with a note that tests were not run.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Updated `tests/src/jakarta.el/jakarta.el-api/4.0.0/src/test/java/jakarta_el/jakarta_el_api/FactoryFinderTest.java`.\n\nWhat changed:\n- Refined the null context class loader test to use the supported `ExpressionFactory.newInstance()` system-property lookup path.\n- This should drive `FactoryFinder.newInstance()` through:\n  - `Class.forName(String)` when the context class loader is `null`\n  - `Class#getDeclaredConstructor(Class[])`\n  - `Constructor#newInstance(Object[])` for the default constructor path\n- Preserved the existing non-null context class loader/system-property test for the `loadClass` + `Properties` constructor path.\n- Removed the Jakarta service-provider fixture so `ServiceLoader` does not short-circuit the system-property path needed for the remaining call sites.\n\nI did not run tests, per instruction not to compile or run them locally.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0484b4ce47d41ffa016a264596264c81968f5c41998f0255dd\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 485, "output": 661, "cacheRead": 29184, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 30330, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1780893061863, "responseId": "resp_0484b4ce47d41ffa016a26458663c881969bc04796ab17238a"}, "toolResults": []}
